race.comment: The former Victorian KATHY'S ROSE (7) is another strong winning chance for the lethal Wiggins-Taylor linkage. Seeks the hat-trick off a heavily bet first-up win at Townsville in a CL1 and has weight relief in this grade. Will likely push forward and she has more up her sleeve. TIPSY TIGER (8) switched from the premier metro stable and belted the 65 graders at Home Hill by 5L over 800m. The longer sprint won't be an issue and she will have taken improvement. A chance. OUTWITTED (1) was prominent on the corner when beaten a nose over 1300m this track/grade  Has his share of talent. Comes back to 1050m, freshened 49 days and Butler will give him every chance from the inside barrier. SNAZZY SNITZEL (3) has also been freshened and was much better last time beaten a nose here in a 55 from the front. Has a 3kg claim and the speed-bred gelding is in the mix.
